Methods on CSS Selectors:

1).  class name :    we can user class attribute of the element to indentify the element.
            e.g : .text-input
            -->   .inputtext._55r1._6luy --> Facebook website see in class attribute

2).  id : we can indentify element with id attribute using css selectors :
               -> #pass
               -> #email
               -> #u_0_5_Rr   -- For login button in facebook

3).  attribute : get element with attribute in css selector
               e.g : tagname[attribute='value']
               ->input[placeholder='Email address or phone number']
               ->input[placeholder='Password']
               ->[placeholder='Password']
               ->button[data-testid='royal-login-button']
               -> [data-testid='royal-login-button']

4).  start value : e.g : tagname[attribute^='start value']
                    -> input[placeholder^='Email']
                    -> input[placeholder^='Pass']